definition.value: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a 2-phenoxypropanamido group.

A 2-acetyl-1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine betaine which has octadecyl as the alkyl group. PAF is a potent phospholipid activator and mediator of many leukocyte functions, including platelet aggregation, inflammation, and anaphylaxis.
A compound based on an indole skeleton, containing one or more halogen atoms
A compound based on an indole skeleton, containing one or more chlorine atoms
A chloroindole that is a compound based on an indole skeleton with a chlorine atom bonded to the nitrogen atom of the indole.
An organobromine compound that is a compound based on an indole skeleton, containing one or more bromine atoms.
A compound based on an indole skeleton with a bromine atom bonded to the nitrogen atom of the indole.
A diterpenoid with a tetracyclic skeleton.
A chondroitin sulfate in which the site of sulfation is positions 4 and 6 of the N-acetylgalactosamine (GalNAc) sugar.
A 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate in which the 1-alkyl substituent can be any alk-1-enyl group.
A glycerophosphate compound having an alkyl substituent at the 2-position of the glycerol moiety and its phosphorus acid component esterified with choline.
A butanediol in which the two hydroxy groups are located at positions 1 and 2.
A butanediol compound having two hydroxy groups in the 1- and 3-positions.
A member of the class of butanediols that is butane in which two of the hydrogens have been replaced by hydroxy groups.
A butane-1,2-diol of R-configuration.
A butane-1,2-diol of S-configuration.
A butane-1,3-diol of R-configuration.
A butane-1,3-diol of S-configuration.
The hydrochloride monohydrate of bepridril.
L-Cysteine substituted at nitrogen by an acetyl group and at sulfur by a substituted-lactam carbonyl group.
The dihydrate of a tris(1,10-phenanthroline)ruthenium(2+) dichloride salt.
A magnesium salt of a bis-sulfonated phenylazonaphthalene.

A monocarboxylic acid that is 4-oxo-1,4-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid which is substituted on the nitrogen by a cyclopropyl group and at positions 6, 7, and 8 by fluoro, 3-methylpiperazin-1-yl, and methoxy groups, respectively. Gatifloxacin is an antibiotic of the fourth-generation fluoroquinolone family, that like other members of that family, inhibits the bacterial topoisomerase type-II enzymes.
A cationic phosphosphingolipid consisting of sphingosine having a phosphocholine moiety attached to its primary hydroxyl group.
A mixture of peptides and proteins produced by partial hydrolysis of collagen extracted from the skin, bones, and connective tissues of animals such as domesticated cattle, chicken, pigs, and fish.

An ansamycin consisting of a 19-membered macrocyle incorporating a benzoquinone ring and a lactam functionality. It shows antimicrobial activity against many Gram-positive and some Gram-negative bacteria.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-tetraphosphate compound having a 5'-adenosyl residue at the P(1)-position and a 5'-guanosyl residue at the P(4)-position.

A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of L-asparagine at the amino group, the carboxy group, or the carboxamide, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-asparagine by a heteroatom.
A metal sulfate having nickel(2+) as the metal ion.
A naphthalenediamine compound having amino substituents in the 1- and 5-positions.
A naphthalene substituted with two amino groups.
A cytidine 3'-phosphate compound with a monophosphate group at the 3'-position.
A monocarboxylic acid amide  having an N-(5-carboxypentyl) substituent and a C-(4-hydroxy-3-nitrophenyl) substituent.

An amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of lysine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of lysine by a heteroatom. The definition normally excludes peptides containing lysine residues.
A carboxamide compound having an N-(5-carboxypentyl) substituent and a C-(4-hydroxy--5-iodo-3-nitrophenyl) substituent.
Caffeine substituted at its 8-position by an (E)-3-chlorostyryl group.
An ester of N-hydroxysuccinimide.
A norterpene that is an acyclic saturated hydrocarbon derived from phytane by loss of its C-16 terminal methyl group.
A carotenone compound arising from oxidative cleavage of the 5',6'-double bond.
A macromolecule composed of units connected by ether (-O-) linkages.
A polymer composed of units connected by amide (-NR-C(=O)-) linkages, where R can be H or organyl.
